[PROJECT]
 - Complete documentation on every single part of the code for the sake of my life
 - Less spaghet code

[BUILD SYSTEM - built on top of `spice.compilation` / `spice.compilation.pipeline` - should have >= build.gradle level of control for buildflow]
 - Lift LOOKUP_PATHS / RESOLVED_FILES off module globals onto the context/Project object (the one source-of-truth obj)
 - spice.compilation.task primitive: a task is (inputs, outputs, action, pure) — inputs/outputs needed or you get ordering without caching
 - Caching = total-state hash taken *before* the task; same pre-state hash across runs -> skip. skip == replay cached post-state (snapshot SpiceFile)
 - `pure` contract declared at task def: gates skip/cache + parallel scheduling. cacheable = pure AND all ancestors pure (purity is transitive)
 - Plugins (1.0+) = event bus: push the live SpiceFile at each pipeline stage to every subscribed entry point
 - build.spice.py / build.spice.spc - the name is not hard coded, its just convention / default. CLI would look for build.spice.spc -> main.spc for entry points.